I do not see Law and Justice being ousted from power.

It will be close, but with a new candidate on the civic ballot and the current administration being rocked by corruption a change will take place. This will be a reoccurring theme throughout the 2020 election cycle.

So last time around when an election happened back when there was an election. The Law and Justice represenentives were leading in the polls by 20 points. The country is going more and more nationalistic. Probably will update later when I do some more research.
2015: - Plurality in first round, majority in second - Incumbent didn't win. - Winner: Law and Justice

I wasn't able to find polls since the new leader for the Civic Platform was chosen. I assumed a median outcome of the new leader will be a return to the polling that the Civic Platform was getting at the beginning of the year, but down-weighted a little bit because I think the Law & Justice candidate is likely to get a continued boost from the current crisis.
